This paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category as it focuses on comparing the performance of TCP and QUIC protocols. It could also fall under the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category as it discusses the security aspects of QUIC. Additionally, the paper includes user studies, which could place it in the Multimedia (cs.MM) or Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) categories. Finally, the paper's focus on user experience could also make it relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) category.
